  "body": "`ts-node` works very differently than tsc. It ignores the `tsconfig.json`'s `files`, `include` and `exclude` entries and only considers files that are imported.\r\n\r\nThe problem with this approach is that Buidler plugins normally use ambient module augmentation to extend types (i.e. `.d.ts` redefining interfaces). These files are never included, but specified in `tsconfig.json`'s `files`.\r\n\r\n`TS_NODE_FILES=true` prevents `ts-node`  from ignoring those entries. We should define it, unless `TS_NODE_FILES=false` is present.",
